    <q>the Internet</q>, using technology patterns <ins>as appropriate markup languages ​​for display on Internet browsers
    or other user interfaces built in the Internet.</ins><br>
	Any website on the Internet consists of three basic elements <q>the name and address of the site -
	the server on which the site files are located - the site files itself that are presented to the user</q>. 
	The process of designing any website requires dealing with these three elements because it complements 
	some of them in order for the website to finally appear on the Internet.
